00:50:24.719 --> 00:50:32.159
but we were able to use it on the job, right? We had to convert this big code base from Pandas

00:50:32.159 --> 00:50:38.320
to Polars and R to Python. And I just knew that as long as we were one step ahead,

00:50:39.040 --> 00:50:47.760
we could figure things out as we go and we could write this book. So about Polars, a couple of

00:50:47.760 --> 00:50:58.560
things, well, what I didn't expect, the little things, the little things. When you are writing

00:50:58.560 --> 00:51:05.919
a book, you take a somewhat of a higher level view and then you start to notice missing things,

00:51:06.479 --> 00:51:13.280
right? Polars is back, especially a year ago, very much under development. So you start to

00:51:13.919 --> 00:51:19.679
